   6. FAQ — Editorial accordion
   ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}
<section class="ep-faq">
  <div class="ep-faq-inner">
    <div>
      <span class="ep-chapter-label">Common Questions</span>
      <h2 class="ep-faq-title">SDBA FAQ</h2>
      <p class="ep-faq-sub">The questions savers actually ask about Self-Directed Brokerage Accounts and professional management.</p>
      <a href="/services/sdba/faq/" class="ep-btn-ghost" style="margin-right:0.5rem;">View All SDBA FAQs</a>
      <a href="/contact/" class="ep-btn-primary">Ask About SDBAs</a>
    </div>
    <div>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">What is a Self-Directed Brokerage Account (SDBA)? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>An SDBA is a feature within your employer retirement plan (401(k), 403(b), 457, 401(a), or federal TSP) that lets you invest in thousands of mutual funds and ETFs beyond the standard fund lineup. Think of it as a brokerage window inside your retirement plan — same tax treatment, same employer match, dramatically more investment options.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">Does my retirement plan offer an SDBA? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>Many mid-to-large employers and the federal TSP do — but plans rarely advertise it. Common SDBA platforms include Fidelity BrokerageLink, Schwab PCRA, Empower Brokerage, and Vanguard Brokerage Option. A Capital Wealth advisor can confirm your plan's eligibility on a complimentary 30-minute call.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">Does my money leave my employer's 401(k) plan? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>No. This is one of the most important things to understand about an SDBA — your money never leaves your 401(k). The brokerage window is an account <em>inside</em> your existing plan. You keep your employer match, your tax treatment, and your ERISA creditor protections. No rollover, no distribution, no taxable event.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">How is an SDBA different from a target-date fund? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>Target-date funds assume every participant of a given age has the same savings, the same risk tolerance, the same outside assets, and the same tax picture — which simply isn't true. A professionally managed SDBA lets us build an allocation around <em>your</em> timeline, <em>your</em> other accounts, and <em>your</em> risk comfort, and monitor it in real time.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">Can my financial advisor manage my SDBA? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>Yes — that's exactly what we do. Most advisors can't access your workplace plan, which is why so many 401(k)s sit unmanaged. The SDBA creates a bridge that lets Capital Wealth manage your retirement plan investments alongside your IRAs and taxable accounts as one coordinated portfolio.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">How much does an SDBA cost? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>Plan providers typically charge a small annual SDBA account fee (often $25–$50), plus fund expense ratios and any trading costs. Our advisory fee is transparent, disclosed upfront, and billed directly against the account — never as a hidden commission inside a fund.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">What are the 2026 401(k) contribution limits? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>For 2026, the IRS limit for employee contributions to a traditional or Roth 401(k) is $24,500. Age 50+ can add an $8,000 catch-up for a total of $32,500. Ages 60–63 may add a $11,250 SECURE 2.0 "super catch-up" where the plan allows, for a total of $34,750. Employer match and profit-sharing are on top of those limits.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">What happens to my SDBA if I leave my job? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>You generally have four options: leave the balance in your former employer's plan, roll it into your new employer's 401(k), roll it into an IRA, or take a distribution (usually not advisable). Each has different implications for fees, investment options, creditor protection, and advice — we'll help you weigh them when the time comes.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">Do I still control my 401(k) if Capital Wealth manages my SDBA? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>Yes. You retain full control of your 401(k) account and plan participation. Capital Wealth manages the investment selection inside the Self-Directed Brokerage Account as your fiduciary — you can pause, modify, or cancel SDBA management at any time without affecting the rest of your 401(k).</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">Can I see my SDBA in my regular 401(k) account online? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>Yes. Your SDBA appears as an investment position inside your normal 401(k) or TSP online account. For detailed holdings, you can also log in directly to the brokerage platform (Fidelity, Schwab, Empower, Vanguard, or TSP) that powers the SDBA.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">How do I know which investments are right for me inside an SDBA? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>Your Capital Wealth fiduciary advisor builds your SDBA portfolio around your age, retirement timeline, risk tolerance, existing assets, and income needs. Selection and ongoing rebalancing are handled for you — no DIY fund-picking required.</p></div>
      </button>
